1.title: A Regal Life (Pilot)
1.plot: The inaugural episode finds Ryan Wyatt, in desperate need of a job after multiple flame outs since graduating college, finds himself at Royal Cinemas to try and re-ignite his long forgotten filmmaking spark. On his first day, Ryan not only learns what his new job entails, but, also finds himself in the midst of a heated employee vs employee battle as a new shift lead promotion hangs in the balance. Adam takes Ryan along with a plot to keep a rather self-important employee out of the promotion while Oscar shows Ryan the ropes.

imdb.plot outline: After finding himself disillusioned with the job market, frustrated college graduate Ryan Wyatt moves back home and takes the first job he can find: working at the local movie theater. What looked like free movies and an easy paycheck quickly becomes a job where Ryan find's himself dealing with irate customers, corporate non-sense, and some wildly eccentric co-workers. The carnival show that is life at Royal Cinemas wouldn't be possible without it's dubious collection of cast members...welcome to the team.
imdb.title: The Cast Members
plot: A modern take on Clerks meets The Office and Superstore as a group of rag-tag employees at movie-theater chain Royal Cinemas try to find time for work between battling customers, management and sometimes themselves.::Aaron Roberts - Exec Producer
